<subSubSection pageId="3" pageNumber="4" type="nomenclature">
<paragraph blockId="3.[95,467,1466,1523]" pageId="3" pageNumber="4">
<heading centered="true" fontSize="10" level="2" pageId="3" pageNumber="4" reason="5">
<taxonomicName authority="Kotov &amp; Elmoor-Loureiro, 2008" authorityName="Kotov &amp; Elmoor-Loureiro" authorityYear="2008" class="Branchiopoda" family="Ilyocryptidae" genus="Ilyocryptus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diplostraca" pageId="3" pageNumber="4" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="subSpecies" species="cuneatus" subSpecies="brasiliensis">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[95,467,1466,1491]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="4">Ilyocryptus cuneatus brasiliensis</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation author="Kotov, A. A. &amp; Elmoor-Loureiro, L. M. A." box="[95,460,1498,1523]" pageId="3" pageNumber="4" pagination="49 - 64" refId="ref4539" refString="Kotov, A. A. &amp; Elmoor-Loureiro, L. M. A. 2008. Revision of Ilyocryptus Sars, 1862 (Cladocera: Ilyocryptidae) of Brazil whit description of two new subspecies. Zootaxa, 1962: 49 - 64." type="journal article" year="2008">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[95,460,1498,1523]" pageId="3" pageNumber="4">Kotov &amp; Elmoor-Loureiro, 2008</emphasis>
</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
</heading>
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="3.[95,720,1562,2035]" pageId="3" pageNumber="4">Sub-ovoid body, dorsal keel present but not developed, molting incomplete; setae on the posterior margin of valves armed with relatively long and slender setae, spines unilaterally inserted, without setulae; posteriormost setae on the valves armed with setulae. Head triangular shaped, fornices prominent, projection on the mandibular articulation present; dorsal pore high in relation dorsal line. Postabdomen relatively short, preanal part longer than postanal;5-10 marginal denticles on the preanal part, duplicated; anal part short with 5-6 short lateral setulae; seven marginal spines on the postanal part; distalmost part of postanal part with 4-5 rudimentary lateral setae, up seven lateral setae which are slightly longer than marginal spines; basal spines on the postabdominal claw of similar length.</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="3" pageNumber="4" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="3.[95,718,2074,2131]" lastBlockId="3.[794,1419,1370,1587]" pageId="3" pageNumber="4">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[95,230,2074,2099]" pageId="3" pageNumber="4">Comments:</emphasis>
<taxonomicName authorityName="Kotov &amp; Elmoor-Loureiro" authorityYear="2008" box="[239,587,2074,2099]" class="Branchiopoda" family="Ilyocryptidae" genus="Ilyocryptus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diplostraca" pageId="3" pageNumber="4" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="subSpecies" species="cuneatus" subSpecies="brasiliensis">
<emphasis box="[239,587,2074,2099]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="4">Ilyocryptus cuneatus brasiliensis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is the only Neotropical taxon of a group composed almost exclusively of Palearctic species. This appears to be rare, with a range restricted to two localities in the state of 
<collectingRegion country="Brazil" name="Sao Paulo" pageId="3" pageNumber="4">São Paulo</collectingRegion>
, belonging to the 
<collectingRegion box="[1059,1134,1434,1459]" country="Brazil" name="Parana" pageId="3" pageNumber="4">Paraná</collectingRegion>
River Hydrographic Basin (
<figureCitation box="[801,884,1466,1491]" captionStart="Figure 3" captionStartId="5.[94,153,2074,2099]" captionTargetBox="[114,1398,333,2043]" captionTargetId="figure-49@5.[113,1398,332,2044]" captionTargetPageId="5" captionText="Figure 3. Geographic distribution Ilyocryptidae Smirnov 1976 emend.Smirnov,1992 taxa of Brazil. (A) Ilyocryptus cuneatus brasiliensis.(B) Ilyocryptus paranaensis inarmatus.(C) Ilyocryptus paranaensis paranaensis.(D) Ilyocryptus plumosus.(E)Ilyocryptus silvaeducensis paraensis.(F) Ilyocryptus sarsi.(G) Ilyocryptus spinifer." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4613808" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4613808/files/figure.png" pageId="3" pageNumber="4">Fig. 3A</figureCitation>
). For further information concerning the morphology of this taxon and its differentiation from other subspecies occurring in other zoogeographical zones, see 
<bibRefCitation author="Kotov, A. A. &amp; Elmoor-Loureiro, L. M. A." box="[837,1188,1562,1587]" pageId="3" pageNumber="4" pagination="49 - 64" refId="ref4539" refString="Kotov, A. A. &amp; Elmoor-Loureiro, L. M. A. 2008. Revision of Ilyocryptus Sars, 1862 (Cladocera: Ilyocryptidae) of Brazil whit description of two new subspecies. Zootaxa, 1962: 49 - 64." type="journal article" year="2008">Kotov &amp; Elmoor-Loureiro (2008)</bibRefCitation>
.
</paragraph>
